WEBVTT

00:26.861 --> 00:29.029
[waves lapping]

00:31.824 --> 00:34.660
[birds chirping]

00:43.419 --> 00:46.672
[Greg] I have a picture
in my head of a place.

00:48.048 --> 00:49.967
Home.

00:51.177 --> 00:52.470
A woman.

00:53.929 --> 00:56.974
I don’t know
if any of it’s real,

00:57.057 --> 00:59.226
but it has a feeling,

00:59.310 --> 01:01.520
and the feeling’s real.

01:03.355 --> 01:05.524
♪ ♪

01:18.829 --> 01:20.873
[man] I’m sorry you’re having
technical difficulties.

01:20.956 --> 01:22.541
-[busy chatter]
-[phones ringing]

01:22.625 --> 01:25.252
Yeah. You know what?
I’m gonna transfer you.

01:26.337 --> 01:27.713
-[phone ringing]
-Hold on.

01:27.797 --> 01:30.132
[woman] I’m sorry you’re having
technical difficulties.

01:30.216 --> 01:32.718
-What seems to be the problem?
-[phone continues ringing]

01:32.802 --> 01:34.428
[ringing continues faintly]

01:34.512 --> 01:37.681
-[waves lapping]
-[birds chirping]

01:42.686 --> 01:44.480
-[ringing stops]
-Seriously, what the "F"?

01:44.563 --> 01:46.607
Wittle’s not picking up
his phone again.

01:48.317 --> 01:52.404
[cell phone vibrating]

01:55.658 --> 01:57.827
-Hi, my love.
-[Emily] Hi.

01:57.910 --> 02:00.704
I’m so happy you called me back.

02:00.788 --> 02:02.540
-How’s your shoulder?
-My shoulder’s good.

02:02.623 --> 02:06.752
My leg is a little bit achy,
but I’m taking the meds, so...

02:06.836 --> 02:08.712
Enough about me. How are you?

02:08.796 --> 02:10.297
[Emily]
I’m good. I’m good.

02:10.381 --> 02:12.675
Um, I wanted to talk to you
about my graduation.

02:12.758 --> 02:14.552
[Greg] I can’t believe
you’re graduating.

02:14.635 --> 02:16.136
[Emily]
Can’t believe?

02:16.220 --> 02:19.515
-Really? -Oh, it’s hard
to keep track of the time,

02:19.598 --> 02:23.060
but I’m...
I’m really proud of you.

02:23.143 --> 02:24.979
Uh, so, um, Mom is,

02:25.062 --> 02:27.648
uh, she’s getting a reservation
at Cliff’s Edge.

02:27.731 --> 02:29.608
-Okay.
-Um...

02:29.692 --> 02:31.861
Mm-hmm. That’ll be nice.

02:31.944 --> 02:34.321
Well, I want you to come.

02:34.405 --> 02:36.240
D-Does she want me to come?

02:36.323 --> 02:38.784
I want you to come, Dad.

02:38.868 --> 02:40.744
Well, I wonder if maybe,

02:40.828 --> 02:43.831
if I take you and your brother
out the next day and...

02:43.914 --> 02:45.708
Are-are you not coming
to the ceremony?

02:45.791 --> 02:46.917
Of course I’m coming.

02:47.001 --> 02:48.377
I’m gonna be there
in the bleachers.

02:48.460 --> 02:51.046
I’m gonna see you in your...
cap and gown,

02:51.130 --> 02:53.382
walking across there,
and be cheering.

02:53.465 --> 02:55.467
I-I just... I-I don’t want to...

02:55.551 --> 02:58.762
I don’t want to complicate
things with your mom and...

02:58.846 --> 03:02.266
I know that I messed up,
and I just want this to be...

03:02.349 --> 03:05.519
-the focus to be on... Yeah.
-Dad.

03:05.603 --> 03:06.937
[sighs]

03:07.021 --> 03:10.608
I have so many thoughts
I wish you could see.

03:10.691 --> 03:12.776
-[phone ringing]
-[stammers, sighs]

03:12.860 --> 03:15.321
Are-are you, are you sure
you’re okay, Daddy?

03:15.404 --> 03:16.864
I’m...
Yes, I’m better than okay.

03:16.947 --> 03:18.324
I’m great. I just...

03:18.407 --> 03:20.743
Let me... let me...
How about I call you back?

03:20.826 --> 03:22.119
-Okay. All right.
-Okay. I love you.

03:22.202 --> 03:23.621
-Okay. Love you, too.
-I love you. Bye.

03:23.704 --> 03:25.080
Okay. Bye.

03:25.164 --> 03:26.999
[ringing continues]

03:27.082 --> 03:28.918
[sets cell phone down]

03:29.001 --> 03:30.210
Greg Wittle.

03:30.294 --> 03:32.338
[Doris]
Bjorn wants to see you.

03:32.421 --> 03:34.214
-Okay, I’ll be right there.
-[line clicks]

03:34.298 --> 03:36.133
-[stammers]
-[dial tone droning]

03:47.061 --> 03:49.605
-[waves lapping]
-[birds chirping]

03:57.446 --> 03:58.530
Hey, Wittle.

03:58.614 --> 04:00.074
-Hey.
-[phone ringing]

04:01.241 --> 04:02.660
Taking the day off in here?

04:02.743 --> 04:04.662
[chuckles] No.
I was just getting off a call.

04:04.745 --> 04:06.538
Heard the boss wants to see you.

04:06.622 --> 04:08.499
Yeah, I’m headed down there
right now.

04:08.582 --> 04:09.917
I just was speaking with...

04:10.000 --> 04:11.335
What you got there?

04:11.418 --> 04:13.128
Nothing, nothing.
[grunts, sighs]

04:13.212 --> 04:15.923
No, it’s just kind of private,
sort of a...

04:17.049 --> 04:18.884
-Oh, oh.
-Oh, shit.

04:18.968 --> 04:20.678
-That’s okay. That’s all right.
-I’m sorry, man.

04:20.761 --> 04:22.096
That’s okay. Yeah.

04:22.179 --> 04:25.099
Just let me get this phone call.
Sorry. [mutters]

04:25.182 --> 04:27.142
-[Doris] Now, Mr. Wittle.
-I’m... Okay.

04:27.226 --> 04:28.852
I’m... Be there momentarily.

04:28.936 --> 04:31.563
[hangs up phone]

04:31.647 --> 04:35.109
Could you get that door
for me, please?

04:35.192 --> 04:38.320
[overlapping chatter
from other room]

04:38.404 --> 04:41.615
-What seems to be the problem?
-I’m sorry you’re having...

04:41.699 --> 04:43.867
[chatter quiets]

05:10.185 --> 05:12.229
[automated female voice
speaking Spanish]

05:12.312 --> 05:15.190
[automated voice] To refill
your prescription, press eight.

05:15.274 --> 05:17.026
For the...

05:17.109 --> 05:19.361
Please enter
the prescription number

05:19.445 --> 05:21.905
plus the five numbers
after the dash.

05:29.663 --> 05:32.833
You entered prescription number
eight, nine, seven,

05:32.916 --> 05:36.545
nine, seven, eight, four, four,

05:36.628 --> 05:39.381
five, five, nine, zero,

05:39.465 --> 05:41.759
one, one, two.

05:41.842 --> 05:43.761
If this is correct, press one.

05:45.387 --> 05:46.889
We have no record of

05:46.972 --> 05:48.807
-prescription number eight,
nine... -[phone ringing]

05:48.891 --> 05:51.435
...seven, nine, seven, eight,

05:51.518 --> 05:54.146
-four, four, five...
-[Greg] Sorry.

05:54.229 --> 05:55.647
[Doris]
Yeah, he’s on a tight schedule.

05:55.731 --> 05:57.191
I understand,
and I’m coming down right now.

05:57.274 --> 05:59.651
I’m just wrapping up a call.
Thank you.

05:59.735 --> 06:01.653
[automated voice]
...number, press eight.

06:01.737 --> 06:04.656
For the pharmacy department,
press one.

06:04.740 --> 06:06.533
-[pharmacist] Pharmacy.
-Hi.

06:06.617 --> 06:08.202
It’s Greg Wittle, and there’s...

06:08.285 --> 06:11.914
I’m having a little problem
refilling this prescription.

06:11.997 --> 06:13.749
[pharmacist]
You can only refill five times.

06:13.832 --> 06:15.501
-You need a new script
from your doctor. -Uh...

06:15.584 --> 06:18.420
I understand. I’ve only
refilled it four times.

06:18.504 --> 06:21.423
You have to count the first one
in the five, sir.

06:21.507 --> 06:24.134
But why... But that wasn’t
a refill, the first one.

06:24.218 --> 06:26.470
[phone ringing]

06:26.553 --> 06:28.138
Can you hold on just one second?

06:28.222 --> 06:30.307
-I’m just... Hold on.
-[presses button]

06:30.390 --> 06:32.017
-[Doris] Mr. Wittle.
-Racing out the door.

06:32.101 --> 06:33.310
Understood. Sorry.

06:33.393 --> 06:35.562
Goodbye. Thank you.

06:35.646 --> 06:37.106
-[presses button]
-[dial tone droning]

06:37.189 --> 06:39.608
Would it be poss... Hello?

06:39.691 --> 06:42.236
-Hel...
-[horns honking outside]

06:42.319 --> 06:44.571
-[inhales deeply]
-[hangs up phone]

06:44.655 --> 06:46.406
♪ ♪

06:46.490 --> 06:48.826
[jackhammer drilling,
siren wailing in distance]

07:06.552 --> 07:09.847
-[Greg snorts]
-[outside noises fade]

07:15.978 --> 07:18.147
[busy chatter]

07:20.816 --> 07:22.734
[woman] I’m sorry you’re having
technical difficulties.

07:22.818 --> 07:25.445
What seems to be the problem?

07:25.529 --> 07:27.739
[busy chatter continues]

07:32.536 --> 07:34.788
Hi, Doris. Sorry.

07:34.872 --> 07:36.081
Follow me.

07:37.624 --> 07:39.626
[door opens]

07:39.710 --> 07:42.754
He must have stepped out.
You can sit there.

07:45.966 --> 07:48.260
♪ ♪

07:54.141 --> 07:56.310
[toilet flushes]

07:58.187 --> 08:00.480
-[door bangs shut]
-[Bjorn coughs]

08:02.774 --> 08:04.359
Greg Wittle. How are you, buddy?

08:04.443 --> 08:06.278
Good. Good, Bjorn.

08:06.361 --> 08:07.738
Thank you.

08:07.821 --> 08:09.531
Look, uh, I’m gonna
cut to the chase.

08:09.615 --> 08:11.533
Our Indian counterparts
are crushing us,

08:11.617 --> 08:13.202
autobots are screwing us,

08:13.285 --> 08:15.579
-and a lot of this is
because of you, man. -What?

08:15.662 --> 08:16.872
Where’s your head been?

08:18.999 --> 08:21.293
Have you been drawing pictures
of your dream house

08:21.376 --> 08:22.669
instead of answering the phone?

08:22.753 --> 08:24.254
-Is that what that note...
-What time is it?

08:24.338 --> 08:25.380
I’m sorry?

08:25.464 --> 08:27.007
That’s how
you should’ve led this.

08:27.090 --> 08:28.717
You buried the lede, buddy.

08:28.800 --> 08:30.928
We always start with "sorry"
here at Technical Difficulties.

08:31.011 --> 08:32.763
[chuckles softly]

08:32.846 --> 08:35.057
Look, uh, there’s, uh,

08:35.140 --> 08:37.851
no easy way
to tell you this, but...

08:39.019 --> 08:40.270
...you’re fired.

08:40.354 --> 08:42.648
♪ ♪

08:45.609 --> 08:47.486
Greg, you’re fired.

08:52.199 --> 08:53.909
Greg?

08:57.663 --> 09:00.165
The inside of your head
must be amazing.

09:05.379 --> 09:07.965
This is the beginning
of your new life.

09:17.975 --> 09:19.434
♪ ♪

09:19.518 --> 09:21.687
[phone ringing]

09:26.275 --> 09:27.359
Bjorn?

09:35.534 --> 09:37.828
♪ ♪

09:51.300 --> 09:53.635
[man]
Yo, I’ll be done in a moment!

10:05.022 --> 10:07.232
[grunting, panting]

10:22.122 --> 10:23.915
Is he not here?

10:23.999 --> 10:25.167
Not yet.

10:25.250 --> 10:27.377
-[toilet flushes]
-[door closes]

10:27.461 --> 10:29.129
Toilet’s all you.

10:29.212 --> 10:30.881
Well, I’m gonna get some lunch,

10:30.964 --> 10:34.176
and he can give me a call
when he gets back.

10:34.259 --> 10:35.886
[overlapping chatter]

10:35.969 --> 10:37.804
I’m sorry you’re having
technical difficulties.

10:37.888 --> 10:39.556
I’m sorry you’re
having technical difficulties.

10:39.639 --> 10:41.224
-I’m sorry you’re having...
-I’m sorry you’re having...

10:41.308 --> 10:42.726
I’m sorry you’re having
technical difficulties.

10:42.809 --> 10:44.770
I’m sorry you’re
having technical difficulties.

